韩国新冠突破7000例：韩军确诊35人，大邱一公寓封楼。
South Korea's new crown breaks 7000 cases: South Korean army confirmed 35 people, Daegu an apartment block.
界面新闻                      。
Interface news.
界面新闻。
Interface news.
界面新闻是中国具有影响力的原创财经新媒体，只服务于独立思考的人群。
Interface News is an original and influential new financial media in China, serving only the people who think independently.
图片来源：韩联社“ 军队感染新冠病毒确诊人数增至35人，隔离4420余人。
Source: Korean News Agency. The number of people diagnosed with the new crown virus increased to 35 and 4,420 were quarantined.
”韩国中央防疫对策本部通报显示，截至3月7日下午，韩国较当天零时新增274例新冠确诊病例，累计确诊病例升至7041例。
As of the afternoon of March 7, 274 new cases had been confirmed in South Korea, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 7,041, the ministry said.
同一天，韩国防部宣布军队内确诊人数已经增至35人。
On the same day, South Korea's Defense Ministry announced that the number of confirmed army personnel had increased to 35.
截至目前，韩国死亡病例保持在44例，大部分为患有基础疾病的老年人。
So far, the number of deaths in South Korea has remained at 44, mostly among the elderly suffering from basic diseases.
在确诊病例中，有36人病情危重，118人治愈出院。
Of the confirmed cases, 36 were critically ill and 118 were cured.
大邱市和庆尚北道依然为重灾区。
Daegu City and Gyeongshan North Province remain the hardest hit areas.
截至周五，大邱和庆北的累计确诊病例为6133例，占病例总数的90.6%。
As of Friday, the cumulative number of confirmed cases in Daegu and Gyeongbei was 6,133, accounting for 90.6 percent of the total number of cases.
7日下午，由于大邱一社区公寓住户中有46人确诊感染，当地政府宣布封楼集中隔离，以防止疫情扩散。
On the afternoon of July 7, 46 people in a community apartment in Daegu were diagnosed with infection. The local government announced that the building would be sealed off to prevent the outbreak from spreading.
这也是韩国政府首次采取封楼措施。
It is the first time South Korea's government has imposed a block.
这座公寓属于市政租赁公寓，主要面向35岁以下的未婚女性，共有137户，142名居民。
The apartment is a municipal rental apartment for unmarried women under the age of 35 and has 137 families and 142 inhabitants.
卫生部门调查后发现，公寓住户中有94人为新天地信徒。
A survey of the health sector found that 94 people in apartments were members of Xintiandi.
大邱市已于前一天向该楼住户发送短信，要求住户不得出入，快递和外卖服务暂停。
The city of Daegu had sent text messages to the building's occupants the day before, demanding access and suspending express and delivery services.
所有住户将被隔离至本月15日。
All households will be segregated until the 15th of this month.
同样也在周六，韩国国防部通报显示，截至当天上午10点，军队感染新冠病毒确诊人数增至35人，隔离4420人。
Also on Saturday, the Defense Ministry said the number of people diagnosed with the virus had risen to 35 and 4,420 were quarantined by 10 a.m.
在确诊病例中，陆军有19人、海军一人、海军陆战队队员两人、空军12人，国防部直属部队两人。
Of the confirmed cases, 19 were from the Army, one from the Navy, two from the Marine Corps, 12 from the Air Force and two from the Ministry of Defence.
当天，大邱空军所属的一名合同工也确诊感染。
On the same day, a contract worker attached to Daegu Air Force also confirmed the infection.
军方已按自定标准隔离3750多人，共4420多人接受隔离观察。
The military has quarantined more than 3,750 people to self-imposed standards and more than 4,420 people have been quarantined.
根据国防部规定，从本月10日开始，本人或家人曾到过大邱市、庆尚北道永川市、清道郡的官兵和勤务人员将接受预防性隔离。
Since the 10th of this month, according to the Ministry of National Defense, the officers and men of my family who have visited Daegu, Yongchuan and Qingdao counties in Gyeongshan North Province will be placed under preventive quarantine.
有中国、日本、新加坡旅行史人员及其密切接触者也将接受隔离。
Chinese, Japanese and Singaporean travel history workers and their close contacts will also be quarantined.
上月22日开始，军方已经禁止所有官兵休假和探亲。
The military has banned all military vacations and family visits since November 22.
据韩国外交部统计，截至7日下午，全球已有103个国家和地区对韩国采取入境管制措施。
By the afternoon of July 7, 103 countries and regions had taken measures to control South Korea's entry into the country, according to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
其中有36个国家和地区禁止来自韩国各地的人员入境。
Thirty-six of these countries and territories prohibit the entry of people from all over Korea.
日本此前宣布将暂停对韩国的免签政策。
Japan had previously announced it would suspend its visa-free policy towards South Korea.
从9日开始，日本将对韩国入境人员采取14天隔离的措施。
Japan will impose a 14-day quarantine on South Koreans entering the country from September 9.
作为反击，韩国于6日宣布停止日本游客90天以内短期逗留免签制度，并暂停已发放签证的效力。
In response, South Korea on the 6th announced the suspension of Japanese tourists for up to 90 days short-stay visa system, and suspended the validity of issued visas.
该政策同样将从9日开始实施。
The policy will also be implemented from September 9.
世界卫生组织卫生紧急项目执行主任瑞安已经表示，日韩两国针对疫情制定的相互限制入境举措“并没有好处”，呼吁两国抛开政治纠纷，将重点放在防止疫情扩散问题上。
Ryan, executive director of the World Health Organization's health emergency program, has said Japan and South Korea are "not doing any good" in the face of the outbreak, calling on both countries to put aside political disputes and focus on preventing the spread of the disease.
